  "actual_structure": "**Monorepo with Three Independent Platforms**\n\n**Backend (FastAPI + Python)**:\nLayered architecture following domain-driven design patterns. Clear separation between API routes (presentation), services (business logic), graphs (AI orchestration), LLM clients (infrastructure), data access (Supabase), and models (domain objects). Authentication layer intercepts all protected routes via FastAPI dependency injection.\n\n**Web Frontend (React + Vite + TypeScript)**:\nFeature-based page architecture with supporting layers. Pages coordinate multiple hooks and components. Custom React hooks abstract data fetching and SSE streaming. Context API provides global auth state. Shadcn/ui components provide reusable UI primitives. Strict separation between pages, components, hooks, and state management.\n\n**Mobile Frontend (React Native + Expo)**:\nFile-based routing with Expo Router for tab-based and auth navigation. Similar data fetching patterns to web using TanStack Query. Platform-specific storage handling (SecureStore for native, localStorage for web). Inline component patterns rather than separate component layer.\n\n**Key Architectural Decisions**:\n1. Backend graph layer orchestrates multi-step LLM workflows using LangGraph\n2. Real-time updates via Server-Sent Events (SSE) streaming from backend to both frontends\n3. Firebase for authentication, Supabase for data persistence\n4. Shared type definitions across all platforms (backend Pydantic models mirror frontend TypeScript interfaces)\n5. TanStack Query used for server state management in both frontends\n6. Context API used for client-only state (auth) in both frontends"
}
